comment:
Man, I really believed you when you said you were against hypocrisy.  You say you don't like to call for people's jobs, but you sure seem to relish it here.  There is no DOUBLE STANDARD if DIFFERENT COMPANIES behave in different ways.  Disney fired Johnny from Pirates, yes, but Warner Brothers decided not to care about personal life BS and him on for Fantastic Beasts, as they did keep Amber Heard for Aquaman.  Warner Brothers is behaving EXACTLY HOW YOU SAY YOU WANT THEM TO but you're making a big stink about it because Disney let Johnny go.  Warner Brothers have no control over what Disney did.  But you're demanding that they fire Amber because Disney fired Johnny.  Those are some SJW level logic contortions, there, judging ALL OF HOLLYWOOD as one group that where somehow all companies are responsible for what one company did.
If WB fires Amber, as you demand, then they have to fire Johnny, too, or they are not being fair, and the whole of cancel culture escalates yet again.  I have no respect for your "cancel culture for thee, but not for me" stance, here.  I am very disappointed.
